Things are heating up in the South China Sea

7
00:00:17,109 --> 00:00:20,449
as the Chinese regime has a massive confrontation

8
00:00:20,449 --> 00:00:23,040
with Australian warships!

9
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:26,419
Australia is sending warships through the
South China Sea.

10
00:00:26,419 --> 00:00:30,649
The story was first reported by Australia’s
national broadcaster, ABC.

11
00:00:30,649 --> 00:00:33,820
An official described the confrontation between
Chinese

12
00:00:33,820 --> 00:00:37,730
and Australian warships as “polite, but
‘robust.’”

13
00:00:37,730 --> 00:00:41,010
Yeah, well you know what else is robust?

14
00:00:41,010 --> 00:00:44,840
Australia’s international engagement!

15
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:48,489
Clearly we’re on the brink of World War
III.

16
00:00:48,489 --> 00:00:51,020
And what does Christopher Pyne,

17
00:00:51,020 --> 00:00:52,239
Australia’s defence minister

18
00:00:52,239 --> 00:00:56,570
and most annoying man in Australia have to
say about

19
00:00:56,570 --> 00:01:00,739
the most dangerous confrontation of the 21st
century?

20
00:01:00,739 --> 00:01:05,079
He said, “I think ‘confrontation’ is
somewhat of a

21
00:01:05,079 --> 00:01:07,860
tabloid-style description of what goes on

22
00:01:07,860 --> 00:01:11,310
in the South China Sea very regularly.”

23
00:01:11,310 --> 00:01:13,780
Did he say, tabloid?

24
00:01:13,780 --> 00:01:18,390
Uhhh, right, how dare all the media talk about
it

25
00:01:18,390 --> 00:01:20,950
like it was some big confrontation!

26
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:24,340
Oh...they’re all calling it a challenge
now.

27
00:01:24,740 --> 00:01:25,740
Okay.

28
00:01:27,220 --> 00:01:28,960
Uhh, well...you know,

29
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:32,000
the fine journalists over at the Express in
the UK

30
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,720
called it a confrontation that might bring
World War III—

31
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,460
and they’re not a tabloid.

32
